title.narrative: Support for the Electoral Process in Haiti - CEPPS IV (2015-2016)

description.narrative: (Haiti): Within the CEPPS consortium, The National Democratic Institute (NDI) helps to build the capacity of civil society organizations to provide credible oversight of the elections, mitigate the risk of electoral violence, and advocate for the compliance to the 30-percent gender quota. The International Foundation for Electoral Systems (IFES) builds the communications capacity of the electoral commission and works with it to ensure that women, persons with disabilities, and other marginalized communities are fully integrated in the electoral process. CEPPS is reinforcing the electoral authorities' capacity to conduct credible, inclusive, and legitimate elections that reflect the will of the Haitian people; strengthen the capacity of non-partisan election observers; and assist civil society organizations, political parties, and electoral authorities in increasing women's participation as voters, candidates, and poll-workers. A cost extension will allow CEPPS to conduct activities with newly elected officials; bolster transparency, communication between the population and the elected officials. It will also allow CEPPS to build on ongoing activities and be operational in-between elections leading up to the Senate elections to be held in 2016.
